==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English < Latin < Greek {{Unicode|[[ίρις]]}} ('rainbow').

===Pronunciation===
*ī'rĭs, {{IPAchar|/aɪrɪs/}}, /<tt>aIrIs</tt>/

===Noun===
'''iris''' (''plural:'' '''iris''' or '''irises''' or '''irides''')
# {{anatomy}} The [[contractile]] [[membrane]] [[perforate]]d by the [[pupil]], and forming the colored portion of the [[eye]].
#* See [[w:Iris (anatomy)|Wiktionary article on the part of the eye]]
#A similar [[device]] in a [[camera]].
#A [[genus]] of [[flower]]ing [[plant]]s of the ''Iridaceae''' [[family]].
#* See [[w:Iris (plant)|Wiktionary article on the plant]]
#{{mythology}} The [[messenger]] of the [[gods]].
#* See [[w:Iris (mythology)|Wiktionary article on the messenger]]

